      "text": "All deliverables are complete and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n---\n\n### Deliverables\n\n| File | Description | Size |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| **query1.html** | Complete Three.js black hole visualization | 18 KB |\n| **screenshot.png** | Rendered screenshot of the visualization | 367 KB |\n| **operation_sequence.json** | Step-by-step operation record | 3.8 KB |\n\n### Implementation Highlights\n\n- **Ray Tracing**: Backward ray marching with gravitational lensing (pseudo-Schwarzschild geodesic bending), 200 max steps with adaptive step sizes\n- **Ray Construction**: Direct camera-based ray construction using `iCameraPos`, `iCameraDir`, `iCameraUp`, `iFov` — no inverse matrix approach\n- **Accretion Disk**: Explicit ray-plane y=0 intersection each step (prevents disk disappearing on zoom), inner radius 3.0, outer radius 10.0\n- **Doppler Effect**: Tangential velocity dot product with view direction creates brighter-left/darker-right asymmetry\n- **Starfield**: Procedural 3-layer stars with blue supergiants, white, yellow, orange, and red dwarfs, plus breathing/twinkling animation\n- **Photon Ring Glow**: Accumulated glow near event horizon ensures absorbed rays aren't pure black\n- **UI**: Frosted glass card with gradient \"GARGANTUA\" title, control hints, and working `#anim-toggle` checkbox\n- **Tech Stack**: `THREE.ShaderMaterial` + `OrbitControls` with per-frame uniform updates including `getWorldDirection` and `getDrawingBufferSize`",
